text.section:
An unincorporated nonprofit association may:
Pay reasonable compensation or reimburse reasonable expenses to a member or manager for services rendered;
Confer benefits on a member or manager in conformity with its nonprofit purposes;
Repurchase a membership and repay a capital contribution made by a member to the extent authorized by its governing principles; or
Make distributions of property to members upon winding up and termination to the extent permitted by KRS 273A.130.
